docker:
==================
$ sudo yum install docker -y
$ docker --version
$ sudo systemctl start docker
$ sudo su -
# docker images
# docker ps
# useradd dockeradmin
# passwd dockeradmin
typepassword

dockerfile should be created on normal user

$ nano Dockerfile
	FROM tomcat:latest
	RUN cp -R /usr/local/tomcat/webapps.dist/* /usr/local/tomcat/webapps/
	COPY helloworld.war /usr/local/tomcat/webapps/
# sudo usermod -aG docker dockeradmin
# sudo groups dockeradmin
# sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
	change password authentication to yes
# sudo systemctl restart sshd
# ssh dockeradmin@172.31.9.6(docker privateip)
   enter docker password
$ docker pull tomcat
$ docker run -d --name tomcat-container -p 8081:8080 tomcat
$ su - dockeradmin
$ docker rm -f tomcat-container
=========================
Jenkins job for docker
====>
after executing the above commands
login to Jenkins account=>
managejenkins=>system=>ssh servers=>add=>name:Dockerhost
				       =>Hostname:docker machine private ip
  				       =>username:dockeradmin
				       =>advanced=>use password authentication=>enter password that you have 
					created for docker
                                       apply and save

=>jenkins=>new item-=>name,desc,git=>
postbuildsteps==>send files or execute commands over ssh
           ssh server
          name:DockerHost
          transferset
		source file: target/helloworld.war
		remove prefix:target/
   		execute command:
			docker build -t tomcat .
			docker run -d --name tomcat-container -p 8081:8080 tomcat
        apply & save
=====>build success
